Edit->Undo

"Undo" is used to undo or step back in the work you are doing with the
program. The menu tells you the last operation that you did, that can
be undone. For example, if you moved an object , then use "Undo", the
object moves back to where it used to be. The "Undo" menu item
immediately changes to "Redo". This allows you to reverse the "Undo"
action.

Movieola provides only one level of Undo (only the most recent action
can be undone). Multiple levels of Undo can be confusing sometimes.

